U.S. retail-beef prices rose to a
record $4.687 a pound in May, according to Bill Hahn, an
agricultural economist at the U.S. Department of Agricultureâ€™s
 Economic Research Service .  The price was up from a revised $4.623 in April, Hahn said
today in a telephone interview. The price was also up from
$4.443 a pound in May 2011, the USDA said today in a  report  on
its website. The price is a  composite  that includes choice beef
and other beef and hamburger values.  To contact the reporter on this story:
